==== အစဳအဇန် ယောဂ ====
[[ဝှာင်:Bse_class.jpg|alt=|thumb|Jaggi Vasudev conducting the Inner Engineering Program at the Bombay Stock Exchange]]
ကြဴနူ မဒက်ပတန် ဇြပ်သဘင်ဓရ်တုဲ ဝသုဒေဝ် စပံက်ဓရ် အစဳအဇန်ယောဂ ပ္ဍဲကဵု ဇြပ်ယောဂဣရှ (Isha Yoga Center) ပ္ဍဲသၞာံ ၁၉၉၄၊ သီုကဵု တန်ဗတောန် သွက် ဂကောံဝေင်ဓတ်ဟံက်ကဳ အိန္ဒိယ (Indian Hockey team) ပ္ဍဲသၞာံ ၁၉၉၆ ရ။<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ishafoundation.org/component/option,com_newscomponent/Itemid,885/act,view/id,687/|title=Morale-Booster says Bhaskaran|date=26 November 1996|publisher=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Refreshed Team Begins Final Preparation|date=2 December 1996|url=https://www.ishafoundation.org/component/option,com_newscomponent/Itemid,885/act,view/id,688/|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> ပ္ဍဲ ၁၉၉၇ ညးစပံက်တန်ဗတောန် ပ္ဍဲကၟိန်ဍုင်အမေရိကာန်<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Yoga guru touts peace, not religion|date=15 October 1997|publisher=[[The Tennessean]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=It doesn't take a guru to know which way the stress flows|date=17 March 1998|publisher=[[Dayton Daily News]]}}</ref> တုဲ စနူ ၁၉၉၈ စဵုကဵုလၟုဟ် ပံက်ကဵု တန်ဗတောန် သွက်ကောန်ထံင် မဒးဒုင်ဖျေဟ်ထံင် မွဲဇမၠိင်အာယုက် ပ္ဍဲကဵု ထံင်တမိလ်နဒူ ဂမၠိုင်ရ။<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Yoga Brings 'Freedom' to Prisoners|date=16 February 1998|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> <ref name="SingletonGoldberg2013">{{Cite book|title=Gurus of Modern Yoga|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=walBCgAAQBAJ&pg=PP1|date=6 November 2013|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-993871-1|pages=283 –295}}</ref>

အစဳအဇန် မၞိဟ်မတီဂၠိုင်အိုတ်ဂှ် ဒှ်အစဳအဇန် နကဵုက္ဍိုပ်လိက် 'Inner Engineering (ဗဂေတ်စက် အပ္ဍဲခန္ဓ)' မဒှ်အစဳအဇန် မတွဟ်ထ္ၜးကဵု မၞိဟ်တအ် ဗီုမဂွံဂဇအ်ဓရ်ယောဂ ကေုာံ သံဘဝိ မဟာမုဒြာ (''Shambhavi Mahamudra'')<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/report_in-pursuit-of-peace-of-mind_1496488|title=In pursuit of peace of mind|date=20 January 2011|accessdate=25 January 2011|publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]]}}</ref> မဒှ် အစဳအဇန် မဟီုတွဟ် သၟာန်သွဟ် မဆေင်ကဵု ဓရ်ရ။<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://businesstoday.intoday.in/bt/story/3428/1/the-route-to-dharmacracy.html|title=The route to 'dharmacracy'|date=27 November 2008|publisher=[[Business Today (business magazine)|Business Today]]|accessdate=25 January 2011}}</ref> It views depression as the result of a false widespread belief about an ability to change the world according to one’s desires, and offers to teach the technology of mental well-being, to help one acclimatize with unavoidable work rigors.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/The_Politics_of_Time_and_Youth_in_Brand.html?id=wd2cAQAAQBAJ|title=The Politics of Time and Youth in Brand India: Bargaining with Capital|date=2013|publisher=Anthem Press}}</ref> Vasudev has frequently cited a study by the University of California which supposedly found mahamudra to lead to highly elevated levels (221%) of neuronal regeneration in the brain; it has since been noted that the study appeared in a fringe journal published by a discredited alternative medicine advocate and his allies, and that it merely reports lower levels of subjective stress from a medium-sized uncontrolled group practicing yoga daily for six weeks.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev|date=20 June 2019|accessdate=2019-12-31}}</ref>

==== ဓျာန လိင်္ဂ ====
The Dhyanalinga (composed of the terms '' dhyāna'' and ''linga'') is a consecrated sculptural stone structure standing 4.3 metres (13 feet 9 inches) tall.<ref name="berghella-74">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Berghella|2018}}</ref> Its creation and consecration, according to  Vasudev, was his life's mission entrusted to him by his guru.<ref name="mid">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/Midnights_with_the_Mystic.html?id=Q5yjIrrK8E4C|title=Midnights with the Mystic|publisher=[[Hampton Roads Publishing Company]]|accessdate=}}</ref> In 1998, the structure of the Dhyanalinga was ordered and arrived at the ashram, where the Dhyanalinga Yogic Temple was being built to hold it.<ref name="berghella-70">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Berghella|2018}}</ref> After three years of work, the temple was completed on 23 June 1999<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=Dhyanalingam installed|date=26 July 1999|accessdate=|publisher=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref> and opened to the public on 23 November.<ref>{{Cite news|url=|title=A multi religious temple|date=19 November 1999|accessdate=|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> As a meditative space the Dhyanalinga Yogic Temple is not dedicated to any particular faith or belief system<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2003/07/25/stories/2003072501630600.htm|title=Transformation of the inner Self|date=25 July 2003|accessdate=4 June 2011}}</ref> and is open to all visitors irrespective of their religion or nationality.<ref name="berghella-72">{{Harvard citation no brackets|Berghella|2018}}</ref>  A stone pillar named the Sarva Dharma stambha, located at the temple's front entrance, has religious symbols of several religions carved on to it to denote universal brotherhood.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.hinduonnet.com/2001/09/28/stories/13280795.htm|title=Haven for the spiritually inclined|date=28 September 2001|accessdate=4 June 2011|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Haven for the Spiritually Inclined - The Hindu - 28 September, 2001 - Isha Foundation|url=http://beta.ishafoundation.org/component/option,com_newscomponent/Itemid,288/act,view/id,670/lang,hi/|publisher=Isha Foundation|accessdate=17 January 2020}}</ref>

==== ပဋိမာရုပ် အဒိယောဂဳ သဳဝ ====
[[ဝှာင်:IMG_j257.jpg|alt=|thumb|Adiyogi Shiva statue]]
Designed by Vasudev, the foundation built a 112-feet-tall and {{Convert|500|t}} Shiva statue for inspiring and promoting yoga. It was inaugurated by the Prime Minister of India, Narendra Modi<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.financialexpress.com/india-news/pm-narendra-modi-to-unveil-first-112-foot-tall-shiva-statue-in-coimbatore-on-mahashivratri-5-interesting-facts-to-know/563295/|title=PM Narendra Modi unveils first 112-foot tall Shiva statue in Coimbatore}}</ref> and has been recognized as the "Largest Bust Sculpture" by Guinness World Records.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.guinnessworldrecords.com/world-records/458751-largest-bust-sculpture|title=Largest bust (sculpture)}}</ref>

The Tamil Nadu government has since claimed the entire construction as illegal, for which no approval was granted;<ref name="TNM_Illegal">{{Cite web|url=http://www.thenewsminute.com/article/ishas-shiva-statue-has-no-approval-buildings-illegal-tn-government-takes-stand-57938|title=Isha's Shiva statue has no approval, buildings illegal: TN government takes a stand|date=1 March 2017|work=[[The News Minute]]|accessdate=6 March 2017}}</ref> Comptroller and Auditor General's report further states the construction to have flagrantly violated the rules of biodiversity zones.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/cag-pulls-up-tamil-nadu-forest-department-over-unapproved-construction-by-isha-foundation-in-protected-zone-4718781.html|title=CAG pulls up Tamil Nadu forest department over unapproved construction by Isha Foundation in protected zone|work=Firstpost|accessdate=2019-12-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/isha-foundation-flouted-norms-cag/article24393672.ece|title=Isha Foundation flouted norms: CAG|date=2018-07-12|work=The Hindu|accessdate=2019-12-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/environment/isha-foundation-jaggi-illegal-yoga-centre|title=But Why Is the Cauvery Calling?|work=The Wire|accessdate=2020-01-02}}</ref>

==== Other consecrations ====
Vasudev regularly conducts gatherings (''mahasathsangs'') in the Indian states of Tamil Nadu and Karnataka.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2010/12/14/stories/2010121450650300.htm|title=Isha's Green Salem goes on stream|date=14 December 2010|accessdate=25 January 2011|publisher=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref> He also takes spiritual aspirants on annual pilgrimages (''yatras'') to Mount Kailash and the Himalayas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://newindianexpress.com/nation/article113158.ece|title=Isha shows the way|date=29 June 2009|accessdate=25 January 2011|publisher=[[Indian Express]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/lifestyle/report_mansarovar-is-beyond-words_1431882|title=Mansarovar is beyond words|date=1 September 2010|accessdate=25 January 2011|publisher=[[Daily News and Analysis]]}}</ref>

Every year at the Isha Yoga Center, Vasudev celebrates an all-night Mahashivarathri, the annual Hindu festival in honour of Shiva. It is estimated that these celebrations were attended by as many as 800,000 people in 2013.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ishafoundation.org/news/newsclips/2013/Bazaar-15-June-2013.pdf|title=The Lure of Isha|date=June 2013|pages=106–108}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/fashion-label-to-yogi-donna-karan-on-an-indian-holiday/1087745/|title=Fashion label to 'yogi': Donna Karan on an Indian holiday|date=14 March 2013}}</ref><ref name="outlook">{{Cite news|url=http://travel.outlookindia.com/article.aspx?284848|title=Holy Days|date=1 April 2013}}</ref>

=== ဣရှ ဝိဓျာ Isha Vidhya ===
Isha Vidhya, an education initiative, aims to raise the level of education and literacy in rural India by providing quality English-language-based, computer-aided education. There are seven Isha Vidhya Schools in operation which educate around 3,000 students.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hindu.com/2010/04/07/stories/2010040751230200.htm|title=LIC gives grant to Isha|date=7 April 2010|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=2 February 2010}}</ref>

=== Environmental initiatives ===

==== Project GreenHands ====
[[ဝှာင်:PGH_nurseries.jpg|right|thumb|Saplings being readied for transportation at a PGH nursery.]]
Project GreenHands (PGH) was established in 2004 as an environmental organization. Its activity is largely focused on Tamil Nadu. The organization received the  Indira Gandhi Paryavaran Puraskar, the Government of India's environmental award in 2010. The organisation's activities include agroforestry, plant nurseries in schools,<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/2018/feb/07/ishas-green-school-movement-kicks-off-in-kanchi-dist-1769618.html|title=Isha's Green School Movement kicks-off in Kanchi dist}}</ref> and tree-planting in urban centers such as Tiruchirappalli<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Green-Tiruchi-Movement-seeks-to-rectify-ailing-environment/article15768688.ece|title=Green Tiruchi Movement seeks to rectify ailing environment}}</ref> and Tiruppur.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/Stalin-inaugurates-Green-Tirupur-Movement/article16539707.ece|title=Stalin inaugurates Green Tirupur Movement}}</ref>

==== Rally for Rivers ====
The Rally for Rivers campaign, which ran from September to October 2017,<ref name="thirumurthy-tree-planting">{{Cite news|title=‘Why tree planting is not the answer’: Experts question Jaggi’s 'shallow' Rally for Rivers|date=2017-09-06|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/why-tree-planting-not-answer-experts-question-jaggi-s-rally-rivers-68004}}</ref> intended to rejuvenate India's depleting rivers by growing large forests along their banks. Promoted by Vasudev all over the country, the campaign received support from a broad range of celebrities and the urban populace.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/india/rally-for-rivers-isha-foundations-campaign-has-good-intentions-but-minimal-scientific-backing-4022799.html|title=Rally for Rivers: Isha Foundation's campaign has good intentions but minimal scientific backing}}</ref> MOUs were signed with state governments.

However, the campaign has been widely criticized by environmentalists for lacking in scientific basis and shifting the spotlight away from real concerns. Acclaimed water conservationist Rajendra Singh alleges that the campaign is motivated by the goal of money and fame.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/latest/862029/jaggi-vasudevs-rivers-campaign-meant-for-fame-power-money-says-indias-waterman-rajendra-singh|title=Jaggi Vasudev's rivers campaign meant for fame, power, money, says India's 'Waterman' Rajendra Singh|last=Staff|first=Scroll|language=en-US}}</ref>

==== Cauvery Calling ====
The project intends to support farmers in planting an estimated 2.4 billion trees through agroforestry and simultaneously cover one third of Cauvery basin with trees, as a means of conserving it.

The campaign got popular appreciation from politicians and film fraternity; however, environmentalists and public intellectuals rejected the claims, asserting that the program presented a simplistic view of river conservation, especially without accounting for social issues and had a potential to harm the tributaries and accompanying wild life habitats.<ref name=":02">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/cauvery-calling-ngos-urge-leonardo-dicaprio-to-withdraw-support/article29511545.ece|title=Cauvery Calling: NGOs urge Leonardo DiCaprio to withdraw support}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/environment/leonardo-dicaprio-cauvery-calling-civil-society-groups|title=Civil Society Groups Ask Leonardo DiCaprio to Revoke Support for 'Cauvery Calling'}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/n-ram-questions-jaggi-vasudevs-cauvery-calling-asks-why-it-shifts-goal-posts-112838|title=N Ram questions Jaggi Vasudev's Cauvery Calling, asks why it shifts goal posts}}</ref> A Public Interest litigation has been also filed in the Karnataka High Court questioning the huge amounts of fundraising for the movement and the usage of government owned land for a private purpose without any proper study.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.livelaw.in/news-updates/-karnataka-high-court-issues-notice-on-pil-challenging-fund-collection-for-cauvery-calling-project-148186|title=Karnataka High Court Issues Notice On PIL Challenging Fund Collection For 'Cauvery Calling' Project}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/nation/current-affairs/140919/pil-filed-against-cauvery-calling-campaign.html|title=PIL filed against Cauvery Calling campaign}}</ref><ref name=":12">{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/bengaluru/2019/sep/18/pil-to-cap-cash-collection-for-cauvery-calling-project-2035326.html|title=PIL to cap cash collection for 'Cauvery Calling' project}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/hc-notice-to-state-on-plea-to-examine-isha-foundations-cauvery-calling-project/article29443669.ece|title=HC notice to State on plea to examine Isha Foundation's 'Cauvery Calling' project}}</ref>

