== Politics, religion and pseudoscience ==
Critics note that Vasudev shares the sociopolitical ideology of Bharatiya Janata Party and Hindutva.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev|date=20 June 2019}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/politics/why-hindutva-nationalists-need-a-sadhguru|title=Why Hindutva Nationalists Need a Sadhguru}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/948963/how-jaggi-vasudev-has-helped-strengthen-fears-about-muslims|title=How Jaggi Vasudev has helped strengthen fears about Muslims}}</ref> He plays a vital role in Indian right-wing politics, using his suave and seemingly apolitical guru persona to spread an exclusionary brand of non-secular ethno-nationalism to an urban audience.

He advocates a total ban on cow slaughter and deems the Muslim Rule in India as centuries of "oppressive occupation", which were far worse than the British Raj.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev|date=20 June 2019}}</ref> Vasudev has also spoken in favour of the 2019 Balakot airstrike, introduction of a comprehensive GST and Citizenship (Amendment) Act, 2019 whilst deeming the Thoothukudi protests as lynching of corporate industries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/voices/opinion/sadhguru-caa-video-misleading-on-nrc-protesters-gaslighting-attempt|title=Jaggi Vasudev's CAA Video: 22 Minutes of Half-Truths & Gaslighting|date=2019-12-31}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/politics/an-unenlightened-sadhguru-in-king-modis-court|title=An (Un)Enlightened Sadhguru in King Modi's Court}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/video/948364/watch-jaggi-vasudev-wants-students-to-read-caa-before-protesting-but-hasnt-read-it-himself|title=Watch: Jaggi Vasudev wants students to read CAA before protesting, but hasn't read it himself}}</ref> In an interview before Times Now, Vasudev had blamed the left liberal sections of the society for facilitating militancy in Kashmir and lamented about how Kanhaiya Kumar and Umar Khalid (of JNU sedition row fame) were hogging the public limelight instead of being behind the bars.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.asianage.com/life/more-features/040319/fuelling-peace-with-hatred.html|title=Fuelling peace with hatred|date=2019-03-05}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/politics/why-hindutva-nationalists-need-a-sadhguru|title=Why Hindutva Nationalists Need a Sadhguru}}</ref> His understanding of realpolitik and history, as displayed in delivering these stances has been widely criticized.

Vasudev has also been noted as a longstanding purveyor of pseudo-scientific information across a spectrum of topics, aligning to a politico-religious model.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nirmukta.com/2012/07/26/jaggi-vasudev-doesnt-understand-science-or-the-nature-of-the-universe/|title=Jaggi Vasudeva doesn't understand science|last=|first=|date=}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/voices/opinion/sadhguru-indian-mystics-deliver-lectures-top-colleges-india|title=Should Sadhguru be Hosted by India's Top Colleges?|date=2018-09-17}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev|last=Shahane|first=Girish|date=20 June 2019}}</ref>

In 2015, he propagated long-debunked superstitions in his blog, about food turning poisonous and human health being adversely affected during lunar eclipse; the post has been since been broadcast across multiple mainstream media, for years; over a public discourse, he used a rudraksha garland as an 'energy' measuring device to prove his claim.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thewire.in/science/yash-pal-pushpa-bhargava-eclipse-jaggi-panchgavya|title=This Is No Way to Remember P.M. Bhargava and Yash Pal}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newslaundry.com/2018/02/03/lunar-eclipse-super-blue-blood-moon-superstition-sadhguru-jaggi-vasudev|title=How to spread lunar eclipse superstition using science, Sadhguru explains}}</ref> AltNews has documented Vasudev to have perpetuated numerous myths around clinical depression; he had also protested against a potential prohibition on the use of mercury for Indian traditional medicines, despite its extreme toxicity which can lead to death.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/scientific-research-ascertains-mercury-toxicity-sadhguru-continues-endorse-indian-traditional-medicines/|title=Scientific research ascertains mercury toxicity but Sadhguru continues to endorse it for Indian traditional medicines}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.altnews.in/depression-the-myths-falseness-of-sadhgurus-quotes/|title=Depression: The myths & falseness of Sadhguru's quotes}}</ref> His views on the Higgs boson and alleged benefits for the Vibhuti have been refuted by the rationalists and have been labelled as anti-scientific.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://nirmukta.com/2008/11/25/vibhuti-rudraksha-mahatmayam-a-wellness-guide-from-times-of-india/|title=Vibhuti & Rudraksha Mahatmayam: A Wellness Guide from Times of India!}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.livemint.com/Politics/ESRnWFGSsiAL7muro7GGmK/Its-a-battle-for-the-survival-of-scientific-research.html|title='It's a battle for the survival of scientific research'}}</ref> In a talk delivered at IIT Madras, he propounded debunked theories about water memory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.arre.co.in/pov/science-spirituality-and-the-psychobabble-of-sadhguru/|title=Science, Spirituality, and the Psychobabble of Sadhguru}}</ref>

Shashi Tharoor has noted about how the ideology of Hindutva has encouraged gurus to blend religion and pseudo-spirituality into a lucrative business to promote irrationality.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/features/politics/science-is-not-your-enemy-science-hinduism-1.2653600|title=Science is not your enemy}}</ref> Another piece over Scroll.in, on similar veins, documented Vasudev's casting of religious politics into a meta-scientific narrative and popularization of a Hindutva-centered revisionist history featuring atavistic remembrances of a golden Hindu past; among others it consisted fundamental mis-interpretation of Darwin's work followed by appropriating it as something that has been long discovered in India, advocating for Hindu rituals after death since it spared a slow death (as allegedly justifiable from the continued growth of nail and hairs) and claiming of Hindu Tantric 'scientists' being capable of resurrecting the dead by citing the anecdote.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/927625/opinion-the-disturbing-irrationalism-of-jaggi-vasudev|title=Opinion: The disturbing irrationalism of Jaggi Vasudev|date=20 June 2019}}</ref> Babu Gogineni deemed of him as a spiritualist conman, who built a huge business empire by resorting to a mixture of pseudo-science with science, rather than old age magic tricks which were increasingly getting debunked.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/indias-own-carl-sagan-meet-babu-gogineni-science-populariser-hyderabad-70951|title=India's own Carl Sagan: Meet Babu Gogineni, the science populariser from Hyderabad}}</ref>

